<h3>Dialog</h3>
The structure of the dialog will have this form:

<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-73" src="https://myaemjourney.files.wordpress.com/2016/08/dialog_structure.png" alt="dialog_structure" width="372" height="468" />

The property <em>title</em> will hold the actual text and <em>titleid</em> will be the id of the tag. Following is the <em>xml</em> code that creates the structure above:

[code language="xml" collapse="true"]
&lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?&gt;
&lt;jcr:root xmlns:cq=&quot;http://www.day.com/jcr/cq/1.0&quot; xmlns:jcr=&quot;http://www.jcp.org/jcr/1.0&quot; xmlns:nt=&quot;http://www.jcp.org/jcr/nt/1.0&quot; jcr:primaryType=&quot;cq:Dialog&quot; title=&quot;Title&quot; xtype=&quot;dialog&quot;&gt;
	&lt;items jcr:primaryType=&quot;cq:Widget&quot; xtype=&quot;tabpanel&quot;&gt;
		&lt;items jcr:primaryType=&quot;cq:WidgetCollection&quot;&gt;
			&lt;tab1 jcr:primaryType=&quot;cq:Panel&quot; title=&quot;Title&quot;&gt;
				&lt;items jcr:primaryType=&quot;cq:WidgetCollection&quot;&gt;
					&lt;title jcr:primaryType=&quot;cq:Widget&quot; allowBlank=&quot;{Boolean}false&quot; fieldDescription=&quot;Define title text&quot; fieldLabel=&quot;Title Text&quot; name=&quot;./title&quot; xtype=&quot;textfield&quot; /&gt;
					&lt;radiofieldset jcr:primaryType=&quot;cq:Widget&quot; name=&quot;radiofieldset&quot; layout=&quot;anchor&quot; xtype=&quot;dialogfieldset&quot;&gt;
						&lt;items jcr:primaryType=&quot;cq:WidgetCollection&quot;&gt;
&lt;option1 boxLabel=&quot;&amp;lt;img style=&amp;quot;width:auto;height:auto;&amp;quot; src=&amp;quot;/content/dam/header1.png&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&quot; jcr:primaryType=&quot;cq:Widget&quot; cls=&quot;radiocss&quot; inputValue=&quot;h1&quot; name=&quot;./header&quot; xtype=&quot;radio&quot; /&gt;
&lt;option2 boxLabel=&quot;&amp;lt;img style=&amp;quot;width:auto;height:auto;&amp;quot; src=&amp;quot;/content/dam/header2.png&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&quot; jcr:primaryType=&quot;cq:Widget&quot; cls=&quot;radiocss&quot; inputValue=&quot;h2&quot; name=&quot;./header&quot; xtype=&quot;radio&quot; /&gt;
&lt;option3 boxLabel=&quot;&amp;lt;img style=&amp;quot;width:auto;height:auto;&amp;quot; src=&amp;quot;/content/dam/header3.png&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&quot; jcr:primaryType=&quot;cq:Widget&quot; cls=&quot;radiocss&quot; inputValue=&quot;h3&quot; name=&quot;./header&quot; xtype=&quot;radio&quot; /&gt;
&lt;option4 boxLabel=&quot;&amp;lt;img style=&amp;quot;width:auto;height:auto;&amp;quot; src=&amp;quot;/content/dam/header4.png&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&quot; jcr:primaryType=&quot;cq:Widget&quot; cls=&quot;radiocss&quot; inputValue=&quot;h4&quot; name=&quot;./header&quot; xtype=&quot;radio&quot; /&gt;
&lt;option5 boxLabel=&quot;&amp;lt;img style=&amp;quot;width:auto;height:auto;&amp;quot; src=&amp;quot;/content/dam/header5.png&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&quot; jcr:primaryType=&quot;cq:Widget&quot; cls=&quot;radiocss&quot; inputValue=&quot;h5&quot; name=&quot;./header&quot; xtype=&quot;radio&quot; /&gt;
						&lt;/items&gt;
					&lt;/radiofieldset&gt;
					&lt;titleid jcr:primaryType=&quot;cq:Widget&quot; fieldDescription=&quot;Define title id. This is for Page Jump functionality.&quot; fieldLabel=&quot;Title Id&quot; name=&quot;./titleid&quot; xtype=&quot;textfield&quot; /&gt;
				&lt;/items&gt;
			&lt;/tab1&gt;
		&lt;/items&gt;
	&lt;/items&gt;
&lt;/jcr:root&gt;

[/code]

The important part here is the <em>radiofieldset</em> of type cq:Widget and xtype="<em>dialogfieldset</em>" with a sub node called <em>items</em> of type cq:WidgetCollection. Each option then has a property named boxLabel but its value is the rendering of the image. See for example option 1:
<pre>boxLabel="&amp;lt;img style=&amp;quot;width:auto;height:auto;&amp;quot; src=&amp;quot;/content/dam/header1.png&amp;quot;&amp;gt;"

</pre>
But this simply corresponds to
<pre>boxLabel="&lt;img style="width:auto;height:auto;" src="/content/dam/header1.png"&gt;"</pre>
The path is simply the path to the screenshot, where I stored it in the DAM (what follows assetdetails.html) :

<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-74" src="https://myaemjourney.files.wordpress.com/2016/08/path.png" alt="path" width="676" height="39" />

It is important that all options have the same <em>name </em>but that makes sure that only one can be selected. The <em>inputValue</em> is the actual value that an option will deliver and will be used to render the content. In this  case the input values are h1, h2, h3 etc.
<h3>JSP</h3>
[code language="java" collapse="true"]
&lt;c:choose&gt;
    &lt;c:when test=&quot;${not empty properties.title &amp;&amp; not empty properties.header}&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;
            &lt;${properties.header} id=&quot;${properties.titleid}&quot;&gt;${properties.title}&lt;/${properties.header}&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/c:when&gt;
&lt;/c:choose&gt;
[/code]

The property called "<em>header</em>" is used as a tag name. That is <em>h1</em>, <em>h2</em>, <em>h3</em> etc. in our case and renders different types of headers. Furthermore, it would be clever to add a case in which no header is selected. That would be the default rendering.

I wanted to experiment a little bit with workflows and how to start workflows programmatically. So, as an exercise, I created a little component that will start a workflow that I've created.

<!--more-->
<h3>Mission</h3>
I want to create a simple component that is just a button and a title. When the button is pressed, the title changes and informs the user that the workflow is started. The workflow is a simple notification to the administrator.

